To relieve taxpayers of the stress associated with meeting the federal filing deadline, Kona Ice will host its eighth annual National “Chill Out” Day from 11 a.m. to noon Tuesday, April 18. A Kona Ice truck will be parked at Lowes, 4075 W. Ina Road, Tucson, to hand out FREE cups of tropical shaved ice to all who stop by.

Through partnerships with schools, youth sports leagues and other neighborhood organizations, Kona Ice has given back more than $135 million to the communities it serves. To learn more about Kona Ice’s giveback efforts, visit kona-ice.com/giveback-programs.

Accelerating Times Media Group’s expansion into Southern California, the publisher of Tucson Weekly has acquired the @acornnewspapers, with five award-winning brands serving more than 340,000 readers. The acquisition includes five weeklies including the Acorn of Agoura Hills, the Moorpark Acorn, the Simi Valley Acorn, the Camarillo Acorn and the Thousand Oaks Acorn. Link in @timesmediagroup bio!
